title: Add Up The Parts: DGRO Could Be Worth $42 - Nasdaq.com
text: Looking at the underlying holdings of the ETFs in our coverage universe at ETF Channel , we have compared the trading price of each holding against the average analyst 12-month forward target price, and computed the weighted average implied analyst target price for the ETF itself. For the iShares Core Dividend Growth ETF (Symbol: DGRO), we found that the implied analyst target price for the ETF based upon its underlying holdings is $41.88 per unit.
